President Obama will be visiting Lorain County, Ohio on January 22, 2010, as part of his White House to Main Street Tour. During his visit, he will meet with workers, local company managers, small business owners, and community leaders to discuss ideas on how to continue economic growth and increase employment opportunities. The President will spend the day in Lorain County, speaking with residents about the challenges they face and listening to their ideas on improving the economy. More details about the visit, including locations and press coverage, will be announced in the coming days. This tour is part of President Obama's efforts to connect with American families and understand their experiences during the economic downturn. He will be visiting communities across the country to spend time with community members and share ideas on rebuilding the economy.